headline: Rite Aid to Sell Majority of U.S. Pharmacy Operations to Rivals, Including CVS Health Corporation (CVS)
summary: Rite Aid has sold the pharmacy operations of more than 1,000 of its U.S. stores to major competitors, including CVS Health Corporation (NYSE:CVS), Walgreens, Albertsons, and Kroger, as part of its ongoing Chapter 11 bankruptcy process. CVS Health Corporation (NYSE:CVS) emerged as the largest buyer, acquiring prescription records from over 600 Rite Aid locations across […]
